      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the base",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Crush the {{digestive-biscuits}} to fine crumbs. Mix with the melted {{unsalted-butter}}. Press into the base of the springform tin. Bake at 160°C fan for 10 minutes to set the base. Remove and leave to cool.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the filling",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Reduce the oven to 150°C fan. Beat the {{full-fat-cream-cheese}}, {{caster-sugar}}, {{vanilla-extract}}, and {{plain-flour}} together until smooth, do not incorporate too much air. Add the {{free-range-eggs}} one at a time on a low speed. Add the {{double-cream}} and mix until just combined.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake in a water bath, 65 to 70 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Wrap the outside of the springform tin in two layers of foil. Pour the filling over the base. Place the tin inside a deep roasting tin and pour in enough hot water to come halfway up the side of the springform tin. Bake for 65 to 70 minutes until the edges are set and the centre wobbles like jelly. Turn off the oven, prop the door open slightly, and leave the cheesecake inside for 1 hour. Refrigerate for at least 8 hours before unmoulding.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
